{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"18252f6d-a99c-46c1-8449-667517a7be83","content":"It's a straightforward change. In your project file, simply **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove this line (or set to false): -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**What this does:**\n- `MSTest.Sdk` 3.8+ uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** by default. Setting `UseVSTest` to `true` was opting *out* of it. Removing it opts you back in.\n\n**Other things to be aware of:**\n\n1. **CLI change** — Use `dotnet run` (the test app is now an executable) or `dotnet test` (which still works but delegates to the new platform).\n2. **VSTest-specific adapters** — If you rely on third-party VSTest adapters (e.g., custom loggers/data collectors), verify they support Microsoft.Testing.Platform or find equivalents.\n3. **CI/CD** — If your pipelines parse TRX files, the new platform still supports `--report-trx` via the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package (auto-included by the SDK).\n4. **Runsettings** — `.runsettings` files aren't used by default; configuration moves to CLI args or code. If you depend on runsettings, you may need to migrate those settings.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"de75efab-57f2-46de-8a9d-d8a4c9305d89","outputTokens":365,"requestId":"0426:225F33:1DA6534:217BD91:69E81A86"},"id":"e91bccb5-4d52-49ad-8928-ffe2aa4defb3","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:47:12.391Z","parentId":"34fdc8b5-35f2-4627-8aee-c84cd72fb27d"}
